    "content": "Officials of the Sathyamangalam Tiger Reserve in Erode district on Saturday seized 92 crude bombs , used for killing wild boars , and arrested three poachers near Thalavadi in the Tamil NaduKarnataka border . According to official sources , the poachers , who were travelling on a two-wheeler in Arukkalwadi village near Thalavadi , were spotted during a c Cases were filed against the arrested persons under Section 9 ( No person shall hunt any wild animal specified in Schedules I , II , III and IV ) and Section 32 Ban on use of injurious substances ( No person shall use in a sanctuary , chemicals , explosives or any other substances which may cause injury to or endanger , any wildlife in a sanctuary ) of Wildlife Protection Act of 1972 . The police would also file cases under the Arms Act . Explaining how an explosive is made , a senior forest officer says ammonium nitrate powder sulphur and glass pieces are mixed and made like a marble . The mixture is covered with food item and placed on land to attract animals . The moment an animal bites , it is killed in a blast . Then , the poachers collect the meat and is consumed or sold . OPEN", 
